Cambiamento is the latest album of the band of squallor, published in 1994.

"Cambia Mento", whose title is almost a double meaning, on the one hand due to the sounds on the disc, the other perhaps due to the health problems of Savio, at the time, due to throat cancer, which has become devoid of the vocal cords so that only Cerruti could handle the vocals.

In short, it pulls looked so good in the house Squallor on the personal side. This disc, however, like its predecessors, has not recently two masterpieces: the first is "Albachiava" real mockery against Vasco Rossi (sounds reminiscent of that Evergreen) sung by Gigi Sabani never forgotten (!), and characterized by a tail capable of rolling with laughter ("Hello public", "There is none, you're all alone!"), the second is "Pierpaolo Saturday Evening," another chapter in the saga Pierpaolo, this time focusing on the world of nightclubs (the groove dancereccio is proof).

Nevertheless, there are other times very valid, in their typical style, such as the romantic "Filumena" (again sung by Sabani), "Berta 2: Change" (17 years after the first act), "Preservame Atu" (pun on 'love and on condoms) and the classic funny narratives typical of Cerruti ("Acqua Marcia," "Mafia").
